The weekend brought tragedy after a man was killed in a freak accident under the M41 bridge in the vicinity of the uMhlanga interchange on Saturday. Shortly after 4.20pm Life Response paramedics were dispatched to the single
vehicle accident on the N2 northbound under the M41 bridge where paramedics found a single vehicle that lost control and collided with the bridge. Spokesperson for Life Response 24/7, Leon Fourie said that the driver of the vehicle got out after the accident and was knocked by a passing vehicle. “Paramedics found that due to the serious nature of his injuries he passed away prior to their arrival. The passenger sustained moderate injuries and was treated on scene before being transported to a nearby hospital,” Fourie said. He added that the cause of the accident is unknown at this stage and will be further investigated by SAPS, Metro Police and RTI who were on scene.